@andor44 good point! actually we're doing a lot of background work (for now in Ruby) to support a real integration config: https://github.com/DataDog/dd-trace-rb/pull/203

Even if Python uses different idioms, the idea is to provide a clean way to activate and configure at the same time one integration. This reduces the need of the `Pin` object, while making it available only for specific edge cases.

When we've finished some of the work around the Ruby tracer where we're testing all of this, we'll port such functionality in a Python idiomatic way.

@kennethreitz Ah! Yes! Thanks!

That would actually be a good addition to the readme, IMO.

As a side note: last time I tried in `pipenv`, IIRC, it failed. I (wrongly) assumed we weren't allowed to put the same package dependency in both sections. I'll try it again and report back on `pipenv` side if I still have trouble.

